        <div type="letter">
            <div type="text">
                <opener>
                    <placeName>Down Bromley Kent</placeName>
                    <date>Dec. 18<hi rend="superscript">th</hi></date>
                    <salute>My dear Sir</salute>
                </opener>
                <div type="transcription">
<p>I am very much obliged for answers which were just what I wanted &amp; quite as explicit as I expected.—<ref target="#foot.f2"/> I have had already occasion to put in a salvo about doubtful identification of plants experimentised on.—<ref target="#foot.f3"/> Cucubalus viscosus &amp; Italicus are extremely sterile together as might have been expected from what you say. All the other forms are extremely fertile, only one degree below normal fertility, &amp; which one degree of lessened fertility may, I believe, be accounted for by the requisite manipulation &amp;c.—</p>
<p>Anyhow Gærtner finds the same slight degree of lessened fertility (or rather a <hi rend="underline">greater</hi> degree of infertility) between Cowslip &amp; Primrose, &amp; the Blue &amp; Red common Anagallis—<ref target="#foot.f4"/></p>
<p>With very many thanks | Yours sincerely | C. Darwin</p> 
                </div>
            </div>
                <div type="tnotes">
                    <note xml:id="tnote.n1">2.1 (or … infertility) 2.2] <hi rend="italic">parentheses over commas</hi></note>
                </div>

        </div>

        

        

